results.snippet: SAN ANTONIO, Tex., March 30 -- Lieut. Col. John H. Glenn Jr. announced from his hospital bed today that he was pulling out of the Senate race in Ohio. The former astronaut said that his slow recovery from a severe head injury barred an active...

byline.original: By RICHARD WITKINSpecial to The New York Times

results.lead_paragraph: SAN ANTONIO, Tex., March 30 -- Lieut. Col. John H. Glenn Jr. announced from his hospital bed today that he was pulling out of the Senate race in Ohio. The former astronaut said that his slow recovery from a severe head injury barred an active campaign and that he did not think it fair to ask "the people of Ohio to vote for a name."
